Assume that spannerOptions.getNumChannels() returns 4. Does this means that we only have 4 available channels?
But why expectedChannels/usedChannelHintss can be [0,1,2,3,...,7]?
I am just curious about the mocking here:
                Long channelHint = (Long) options.get(SpannerRpc.Option.CHANNEL_HINT);
                usedChannelHintss.add(channelHint);
SpannerRpc.Option.CHANNEL_HINT is just a string. How do we construct the map options and channelHint will be become 0,1,2,3...7?

